        <p>The iPhone[5] (retroactively referred to as the iPhone 2G[6] or iPhone 1[7]) is the first iPhone model and the first smartphone developed and marketed by Apple Inc. After years of rumors and speculation, it was officially announced on January 9, 2007,[8] and was released in the United States on June 29, 2007.</p>
